  "text": "Because δ > 0, a off > 0, a on > 0 and 0 < η < 1, 0 < A y (δ) < 1. From linear system theory [CITATION_1] , the sequence {y(j)} j∈N is monotonic and asymptotically converges to y ∞ (δ) = B y (δ)/(1 − A y (δ)). Therefore inf t≥0 x(t) = inf j∈N y(j) = min {y(0), y ∞ (δ)}",
